                Mercury was Nebo, and Venus was the goddess Ishtar.</p><br>
            <p>The ancient Babylonians, Greeks, Persians, Romans and others thought of the 7 Classical Planets as gods and named 
                their 7 days of the week after them. Astrologers retain this definition of the 7 Classical Planets today.</p>
